title: Radiohead Make Epic Return to the U.K. With Greatest Hits Set in London: Best Moments
summary: The band played their first show in the U.K. since 2017 at The O2 Arena in London.
body: British music has had such a banner year in 2025, that Radiohead’s return has flown a touch under the radar. With Olivia Dean , Yungblud , Lola Young and RAYE all conquering the Billboard charts in the U.S., and Oasis putting on the biggest tour of the year, the return of the art-rock fivepiece after an seven-year absence feels low-key in comparison. There is no new music to plug, simply a run of shows in major European cities, and an unpredictable setlist – this is as understated as an arena-headlining band could ever dream to be. That said, 2025 has still been notable for the group. Earlier this year they reassessed their 2003 album Hail to The Thief and worked with the Royal Shakespeare Company for a new production of Hamlet . Elsewhere “Let Down,” an album track from their 1997 opus OK Computer went viral and landed on the Billboard Hot 100 for the first time. Their Spotify monthly listener count now tops 44m users, higher than other British rockers such as Oasis, The Rolling Stones and even The Beatles. All this comes despite a period of relative inactivity. The band’s last LP A Moon Shaped Pool was released in 2016 and the group completed touring for it in 2018. Yorke told T…

title: Here Are 13 Songs Taylor Swift Wrote for Other Artists
summary: Some of the tunes feature the pop superstar, others ended up as vault tracks when she released her Taylor’s Versions.
body: Taylor Swift ’s prolific songwriting skills have endured through the 2000s, 2010s and deep into the 2020s. With 13 Hot 100 No. 1 hits (including “The Fate of Ophelia” with six weeks on top of the chart currently ) and 15 Billboard 200 No. 1 albums (her latest release, The Life of a Showgirl , also sits at the top of that chart for its sixth straight week ), she’s found great success with her catchy hooks, gorgeous melodies, and storytelling powers. Related Here Are All of Taylor Swift’s Title Tracks, Ranked (Critic’s Picks) In addition to her charting accolades, Swift counts the record-breaking Eras Tour on her résumé as the highest-grossing tour of all time, as well as 58 Grammy nods (she and her longtime collaborator Jack Antonoff are tied with the most nominations in the song of the year category with eight), with 14 wins, including four album of the year wins : Fearless in 2009, 1989 in 2005, Folklore in 2021 and Midnights in 2023, the most of any artist. Her pen is spread throughout not just her own catalog, but others’ work too. She’s written songs for Miley Cyrus’ alter ego Hannah Montana, Boys Like Girls, B.o.B, Calvin Harris, Little Big Town, Sugarland, Big Red Machi…

title: In Canada: Music Industry’s Next Generation Unites for Billboard Canada’s First 40 Under 40 Event
summary: Also in Canadian music news this week, Warner Music Canada names two new co-general managers.
body: The next generation of music industry visionaries, entrepreneurs and changemakers showed up in droves for the first-ever edition of  Billboard Canada 40 Under 40 . Yesterday (Nov. 20) at W Toronto marked the first time  Billboard ‘s influential celebration came to Canada, recognizing the executives and innovators shaping the global music business. The night was in partnership with YouTube, W Toronto and Hendrick’s. title: Billboard’s Music Industry Events Calendar
summary: A complete rundown of the most important events across the music business.
body: As part of our continuing efforts to serve the music industry and its creators, Billboard Pro now features a music industry events calendar for readers. The calendar will act as music’s most complete summary major national and international industry events, from conferences to festivals to networking mixers and more. Just as Billboard is music’s must-read source for news, charts and analysis, now it also is the go-to for business happenings.
